    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:1.1",
          "pli": "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, saddhe kulaputte ānisaṃsā. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, a faithful gentleman gets five benefits. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:1.2",
          "pli": "Katame pañca? ",
          "en": "What five? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:1.3",
          "pli": "Ye te, bhikkhave, loke santo sappurisā te saddhaññeva paṭhamaṃ anukampantā anukampanti, no tathā assaddhaṃ; ",
          "en": "The good persons in the world show compassion first to the faithful, not so much to the unfaithful. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:1.4",
          "pli": "saddhaññeva paṭhamaṃ upasaṅkamantā upasaṅkamanti, no tathā assaddhaṃ; ",
          "en": "They first approach the faithful, not so much the unfaithful. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:1.5",
          "pli": "saddhaññeva paṭhamaṃ paṭiggaṇhantā paṭiggaṇhanti, no tathā assaddhaṃ; ",
          "en": "They first receive alms from the faithful, not so much the unfaithful. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:1.6",
          "pli": "saddhaññeva paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ desentā desenti, no tathā assaddhaṃ; ",
          "en": "They first teach Dhamma to the faithful, not so much the unfaithful. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:1.7",
          "pli": "saddho kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati. ",
          "en": "When their body breaks up, after death, the faithful are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:1.8",
          "pli": "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca saddhe kulaputte ānisaṃsā. ",
          "en": "A faithful gentleman gets these five benefits. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:2.1",
          "pli": "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, subhūmiyaṃ catumahāpathe mahānigrodho samantā pakkhīnaṃ paṭisaraṇaṃ hoti; ",
          "en": "Suppose there was a great banyan tree at a level crossroads. It would become a refuge for birds from all around. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:2.2",
          "pli": "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, saddho kulaputto bahuno janassa paṭisaraṇaṃ hoti bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānanti. ",
          "en": "In the same way, a faithful gentleman becomes a refuge for many people—monks, nuns, laywomen, and laymen. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:3.1",
          "pli": "Sākhāpattaphalūpeto, ",
          "en": "With its branches, leaves, and fruit, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:3.2",
          "pli": "khandhimāva mahādumo; ",
          "en": "a great tree with its strong trunk, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:3.3",
          "pli": "Mūlavā phalasampanno, ",
          "en": "firmly-rooted and fruit-bearing, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:3.4",
          "pli": "patiṭṭhā hoti pakkhinaṃ. ",
          "en": "supports many birds. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:4.1",
          "pli": "Manorame āyatane, ",
          "en": "It’s a lovely place, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:4.2",
          "pli": "sevanti naṃ vihaṅgamā; ",
          "en": "frequented by the sky-soarers. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:4.3",
          "pli": "Chāyaṃ chāyatthikā yanti, ",
          "en": "Those that need shade go in the shade, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:4.4",
          "pli": "phalatthā phalabhojino. ",
          "en": "those that need fruit enjoy the fruit. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:5.1",
          "pli": "Tatheva sīlasampannaṃ, ",
          "en": "So too, a faithful individual "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:5.2",
          "pli": "saddhaṃ purisapuggalaṃ; ",
          "en": "is perfect in ethics, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:5.3",
          "pli": "Nivātavuttiṃ atthaddhaṃ, ",
          "en": "humble and kind, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:5.4",
          "pli": "sorataṃ sakhilaṃ muduṃ. ",
          "en": "sweet, friendly, and tender. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:6.1",
          "pli": "Vītarāgā vītadosā, ",
          "en": "Those free of greed, freed of hate, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:6.2",
          "pli": "vītamohā anāsavā; ",
          "en": "free of delusion, undefiled, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:6.3",
          "pli": "Puññakkhettāni lokasmiṃ, ",
          "en": "fields of merit for the world, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:6.4",
          "pli": "sevanti tādisaṃ naraṃ. ",
          "en": "associate with such a person. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:7.1",
          "pli": "Te tassa dhammaṃ desenti, ",
          "en": "They teach them the Dhamma, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:7.2",
          "pli": "Sabbadukkhāpanūdanaṃ; ",
          "en": "that dispels all suffering. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:7.3",
          "pli": "Yaṃ so dhammaṃ idhaññāya, ",
          "en": "Understanding this teaching, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:7.4",
          "pli": "Parinibbāti anāsavo”ti. ",
          "en": "they’re extinguished without defilements.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "an5.38:7.5",
          "pli": "Aṭṭhamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
